Biographical Summary


		   	
Pam Arnold has over 25 years’ environmental management experience in private industry settings.  She is an independent consultant, designing environmental compliance projects, training, and leading project teams to successful completion.  She was most recently designated as the Site Waste Certification Official during the closure of the Department of Energy’s Rocky Flats Environmental Technology Site.  Other projects included Site Environmental Auditor, Compliance Manager, and Site liquids characterization and disposition Scientist.

Pam has an extensive environmental background.  She has written, negotiated, and evaluated environmental legislation and regulation.  She has developed compliance strategies and then performed classroom training and OJT to implement those strategies.  She has designed and implemented environmental audits and surveillance.  As a natural and successful leader, Pam takes on that role in nearly every project assigned.  Some of her titles have included:  Lead, Environmental Compliance Task Force; Manager, Environmental Compliance; Lead, Environmental Auditor; Lead, Waste Certification & Oversight, Waste Characterization Subject Matter Expert, Lead, mined land reclamation crew.  Pam began her environmental career in uranium mining where she obtained the company’s mining and milling permits and NRC license; she also worked on the Environmental Impact Statement in the mid 1970’s.  She moved on to oil shale mining, oil and gas development, and finally completed closure of a Department of Energy nuclear weapons facility, the first one to be closed in the United States.
 
Pam is committed to the protection of the environment in industry through simple, easy to manage compliance systems and strategies.  She is expert at creating strategies that both satisfy regulatory requirements and minimally impact business.

GENERAL:

We specialize in legal and professional services that support sustainable energy development and innovative energy technologies. 
We help design and implement strategies and projects to commercialize and deploy distributed energy resources, including renewables, cogeneration, district heating and cooling and community energy systems, fuel cells, and other emerging technologies.
We also help clients understand how law, regulation and public policy initiatives impact the development and deployment of emerging energy technologies, and we work with clients to shape policy, regulatory incentives and legislation that support their objectives. 
We often assemble, manage and work closely with consultant teams that include specialists in finance, engineering, economics, utility and environmental regulation, and related fields.

TYPICAL SERVICES INCLUDE:

• Assistance to federal, state & local governments for energy planning and programs 
• Analysis of legal & regulatory issues arising under state public utility laws & PUC decisions
• Analysis of electricity restructuring impacts on local energy infrastructure & resource options
• Design & drafting of legislative & regulatory inititatives encouraging sustainable energy resources
• Advocacy in legislative & regulatory forums to support clean & efficient distributed resources 
• Evaluation of ownership, financing, & development structures for innovative energy ventures
• Strategy development & contract negotiation for distributed & renewable resource projects 

REPRESENTATIVE CLIENTS include EPRI, E2I, GRI (now GTI), State energy offices (e.g., CA Energy Commission, WSU Energy Program, Oregon Dept of Energy), CA Power Authority, Energy Foundation, NCSL, DOE, investor- and publicly-owned utilities, cities & counties, distributed resource vendors & developers, etc.

Supplier Rating System
The rating system is unique online platform called Supplier Share.  It allows a member to rate suppliers they have done business with and search for quality suppliers they are considering doing business with.  This environment promotes the sharing of quality suppliers throughout various industries and holds each supplier accountable to deliver a quality product or service.  Suppliers benefit from continuing to provide excellence, and encouraging their clients to rate them in the system.
 
Supplier Classification System
The classification system is called Supplier Class.  This concept is not new.  Our uniqueness comes from our ability to provide accuracy to the process.  BDG’s approach is to capture supplier profile information directly from the client’s suppliers and not from unsubstantiated third party resources.  This approach may provide the supplier with more opportunities via classification identification, and positions the client to feel comfortable about the accuracy of the diversity numbers being reported.  This online system makes available to its clients various options such as the ability to reference the actual profile completed by the supplier, copies of certification documents, standardized tier-2 reporting, and a buyer tracking process.

Supplier Diversity Development:
BeeHive Diversity Group seeks out companies looking to improve their supplier diversity program.  We work with individuals involved in shaping company direction and executing company protocol.  Each of our employees are committed to working with you, our customer, to build a program that is company driven, consumer focused and that defines a model of excellence in the corporate community and beyond.

Application Lifecycle Management (ALM) is a collection of disciplines used to help organizations turn ideas into software in a cost-effective and predictable way. While ALM has been instrumental in making software development projects more successful over the past twelve years, statistics show there is still room for improvement. Current ALM tools are discipline-centric and have process, data, and role silos, which don’t work well in today’s application development organizations. Organizations, too, have functional, technological, and geographic silos. Better ALM practices and tools should help break down these silos and contribute to even more successful software projects. These ALM 2.0 tools should be role-focused, with functional components brought together in a process-centric interoperability framework. Serena’s ALM products are already delivering on the promise of ALM 2.0, with organizations worldwide deploying and utilizing them successfully.
Serena is also leading the efforts to create an open-source ALM interoperability framework through the Eclipse foundation.

They introduced cutting-edge technology with the development of the first US patented catalyst to destroy volatile organic compounds (VOCs).  CCC has a diversified foundation with four major divisions: Catalyst, Environmental, Industrial, and Advanced BioEnergy. The entire company is supported by a multi-disciplined engineering staff and a 24/7 service department. 

Industrial Division
The Industrial Division designs, assembles, installs, starts up and services major air pollution control systems such as regenerative thermal oxidizers (RTOs) and Zeolite wheel rotary concentrators for a wide variety of industrial applications.   Our role is to provide customers with state of the art technology required to meet and exceed regulatory requirements such as MACT and BACT for the capture and destruction of Volatile Organic Compounds (VOC’s).

 Environmental Division
The Environmental Division designs, manufactures, shop tests, starts up and services standard and custom thermal and catalytic oxidizer systems used for site remediation. These projects include soil vapor extraction, dual phase and multi-phase extraction, groundwater pump and treat and air stripper projects. Contaminants frequently include BTEX, MTBE and TBA. CCC offers electric and fuel gas fired designs in a wide range of capacity. 
Our clients include the major oil companies and numerous engineering and consulting companies that focus on the environmental industry.

Catalyst Division
The Catalyst Division features a portfolio of precious metal based catalyst products that we develop, manufacture and supply to the food service, stationary engine, wire enamel, remediation and air pollution control industries. We also develop custom catalysts for special applications like fuel cells and nuclear power recombination of hydrogen gas. Toll coating and catalyst cleaning are also services we offer.
The Appliance Division provides wire mesh, ceramic or metal foil substrate precious metal based catalysts to reduce smoke and odor from self cleaning ovens. With the input from the engineering departments of leading appliance manufacturers, we are able to design; manufacture and supply vent tubes for their various models of ranges and ovens. 
 
Advanced BioEnergy Division
The role of the Advanced BioEnergy Division is to synthesize research, experience and future outlook to create a big picture as it relates to progression and development of new business units. Critical to this path is the need to become familiar with what customers and consumers need and to remain aware of what competitors are doing in the marketplace.  The Division evaluates the benefits, risks, and future implications of CCC’s ideas and that of others.  The ability to visualize potential by leveraging existing core competencies is a critical aspect in managing risk exposure.

GAITS Successfully Transitions over 200 IT Professionals within 30 Days to Begin Department of Energy Contract

Alexandria, VA, July 7 - GAITS, Inc., announced today that it has successfully completed transition activities for over 200 Q and L-cleared IT professionals in conjunction with its recently awarded Department of Energy contract at Sandia National Laboratories. The transition was completed seamlessly within 30 days, with broad-based IT support operations now underway in both Albuquerque, NM, and Livermore, CA.

Tom Asefi, GAITS President, stated that the completion of the transition in the 30 day timeframe was particularly noteworthy given that GAITS had the additional task of selecting a new health insurance carrier as part of the transition. Mr. Asefi said: "With our online employee portal, we were able to quickly obtain census data on the employees, submit Requests for Proposals to several carriers, obtain and evaluate proposals, and select the one carrier that best serves our expanded employee base. These steps were all completed while concurrently maintaining excellent progress with overall transition activities. As a result we achieved 100% customer satisfaction during this period."

GAITS also used a transition program management portal based on the Microsoft Sharepoint software to facilitate knowledge sharing among the transition team, which was led by Randy Randazzo, GAITS Sr. Vice President. GAITS immediately established a local office in Albuquerque, NM, consisting of recruiters and HR specialists with deep experience, including specific experience supporting Sandia operations. The transition team conducted orientation sessions on site and held individual meetings with employees to discuss specific needs and situations. Further, the transition team implemented the proven GAITS recruiting process to fill certain high-priority openings immediately, before the end of the transition period. All employees under this contract hold DOE security clearances at various levels. The employees were recruited or transitioned from 11 incumbent contractors, and the consolidated contract for GAITS represents a significant efficiency improvement for Sandia management.

Subpart 8.6—Acquisition from Federal Prison Industries, Inc. 

8.601  General. 
(a) Federal Prison Industries, Inc. (FPI), also referred to as UNICOR, is a self-supporting, wholly owned Government corporation of the District of Columbia. 

(b) FPI provides training and employment for prisoners confined in Federal penal and correctional institutions through the sale of its supplies and services to Government agencies (18 U.S.C. 4121-4128). 

(c) FPI diversifies its supplies and services to minimize adverse impact on private industry. 

(d) Supplies manufactured and services performed by FPI are listed in the FPI Schedule, which can be accessed at http://www.unicor.gov or by submitting a written request to Federal Prison Industries, Inc., Department of Justice, Washington, DC 20534. 

(e) Agencies are encouraged to purchase FPI supplies and services to the maximum extent practicable. 

8.602  Policy. 
(a) In accordance with 10 U.S.C. 2410n and Section 637 of Division H of the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2005 (Pub. L. 108-447), and except as provided in paragraph (b) of this section, agencies shall— 

(1) Before purchasing an item of supply listed in the FPI Schedule, conduct market research to determine whether the FPI item is comparable to supplies available from the private sector that best meet the Government’s needs in terms of price, quality, and time of delivery. This is a unilateral determination made at the discretion of the contracting officer. The arbitration provisions of 18 U.S.C. 4124(b) do not apply. 

(2) Prepare a written determination that includes supporting rationale explaining the assessment of price, quality, and time of delivery, based on the results of market research comparing the FPI item to supplies available from the private sector. 

(3) If the FPI item is comparable, purchase the item from FPI following the ordering procedures at http://www.unicor.gov, unless a waiver is obtained in accordance with 8.604. 

(4) If the FPI item is not comparable in one or more of the areas of price, quality, and time of delivery— 

(i) Acquire the item using— 

(A) Competitive procedures (e.g., the procedures in 6.102, the set-aside procedures in Subpart 19.5, or competition conducted in accordance with Part 13); or 

(B) The fair opportunity procedures in 16.505, if placing an order under a multiple award delivery-order contract; 

(ii) Include FPI in the solicitation process and consider a timely offer from FPI for award in accordance with the item description or specifications, and evaluation factors in the solicitation— 

(A) If the solicitation is available through the Governmentwide point of entry (FedBizOpps), it is not necessary to provide a separate copy of the solicitation to FPI; 

(B) If the solicitation is not available through FedBizOpps, provide a copy of the solicitation to FPI; 

(iii) When using a multiple award schedule issued under the procedures in Subpart 8.4 or when using the fair opportunity procedures in 16.505— 

(A) Establish and communicate to FPI the item description or specifications, and evaluation factors that will be used as the basis for selecting a source, so that an offer from FPI can be evaluated on the same basis as the contract or schedule holder; and 

(B) Consider a timely offer from FPI; 

(iv) Award to the source offering the item determined by the agency to provide the best value to the Government; and 

(v) When the FPI item is determined to provide the best value to the Government as a result of FPI’s response to a competitive solicitation, follow the ordering procedures at http://www.unicor.gov. 

(b) The procedures in paragraph (a) of this section do not apply if an exception in 8.605(b) through (g) applies. 

(c) In some cases where FPI and an AbilityOne participating nonprofit agency produce identical items (see 8.603), FPI grants a waiver to permit the Government to purchase a portion of its requirement from the Abi

Emissions Technology, Inc. produces a catalyst which when combined with the intake air, mixes in the combustion chamber to create a cleaner fuel burn increasing the power stroke and decreasing exhaust pollutants. Our current models of the Catalyst Combustion System (CCS) are DC-103 and DC-203 with other delivery systems in development.  The catalyst is a mixture of metals typically found in a catalytic converter; therefore, the catalytic converter chemistry takes place in the combustion chamber.  Carbon monoxide (CO) and nitrogen oxides (NOx) are reduced largely eliminating unburned hydrocarbons (UHC), which have been converted to useful energy in the engine.
 
Exhaust Emissions Testing Results on a Detroit Diesel Series 50 diesel engine show CO reduced by 9.3%, HC by 58.3%, NOx by 13.6% and particulate matter (PM) by 42.8%.  In addition to reducing harmful emissions, the CCS has been shown in field testing to reduce fuel consumption by 8-12% in heavy duty diesel engines.  Diesel engines have an average operational life of 25 years.  CCS works in conjunction with other retrofit technologies by decreasing the engine emissions at their source.

Computational math, modeling, simulation, solvers, machine learning,  numerical analysis, programming.
Computational mathematics is a core, enabling technology that can be applied across almost any field of scientific research and commercial industry.  
While it may seem somewhat esoteric, here are two simple examples of how Sparsix can apply its expertise in this area to the benefit of the Department of Energy and its subcontractors:
1.	Accelerating the performance of computationally intensive applications, such as:
o	Programs that simulate complex physical systems or phenomena – anything that is described by partial differential equations.  Applications might include nuclear detonation modeling, plasma modeling, oil and gas reservoir modeling, or diffusion of hazardous materials into ground water.
o	Programs that optimize large and complex systems – anything described by linear programming or mixed integer programming.  Applications might include planning of generation resources for the national power grid, auctioning of financial transmission rights for regional power grids, or integration of renewables and micro-grids.
2.	Analyzing massive data sets or real-time data streams for patterns or anomalies, such as:
o	Programs that analyze data from very “noisy” environments and contain a large amount of “bad” data.  Applications might include inline inspection of oil and gas pipelines.
o	Programs that must act on quickly changing data from fast developing phenomena.  Applications might include analyzing phasor measurement unit data from the power grid to detect and respond to potentially cascading failures before they can spread.

biz_name: OnSite Medical Testing - Lakewood, CO, LLC
comments: I have recently opened OnSite Medical Testing - Lakewood, CO, LLC 3.5 miles from your location in Golden. I currently provide a variety of drug and alcohol testing services for corporate and private clients.  I would be honored to provide NREL's pre-employment, post-accident, and random testing.  While we currently provide traditional lab-based testing through a variety of SAMHSA approved labs, we have just partnered with eScreen which will completely change the testing process to which you may have been accustomed.  eScreen is a web based point of collection system that allows us to run all samples right from the office.  Negative results are provided within 15 minutes of the completed test, right to your desktop.  Any non-negative result will be sent directly to the lab for positive confirmation with a turn around time of 24 hours, instead of 48-72 hours with standard lab-based testing.  Obviously this has huge implications in both the pre-employment and post-accident process.  How nice would it be to extend a job offer to a highly qualified candidate within minutes instead of days? Equally, it would be extrememly beneficial to know if impairment due to drugs or alcohol could have been the cause for an employee's accident at work.  In addition to expeditious reporting, there are no bulky chain of custody forms.  The streamlined software allows you to schedule a donor and simply print an "e-passport" which you send with the employee to our office.  In most instances, that is the ONLY piece of paper ever generated.  The environmental impact with this web-based system is remarkable.  I would encourage you to visit my website (www.5280drugtesting.com) to see a full list of our services and even see a few pictures of the office.  I am an RN, and when I designed my office, I did so with the professional in mind.  Drug testing can make people very anxious for a variety of reasons, but my compassionate care and attention to providing outstanding customer service is what sets me apart.  Please let me know if you would like additional information or to see a demonstration of the eScreen process.  I look forward to hearing from you.

Gas Turbine Technology:

The ISEM Team:

Dr. Jayesh M Mehta, MBA. Founder, President – ISEM, LLC:
Upon graduation, from IIT, Chicago Dr. Mehta joined GEAE, where he was responsible for several of the combustor/augmenter technology programs including Phase I of the NASA HSCT, and a program manager on two Navy initiatives on combustion instability. Between 1993 and 2009, Dr. Mehta has been a key technical lead on a variety of gas turbine technology development programs through DiversiTech, Inc. and TK Engineering Inc. These have included NASA/DOD Phase I and Phase II SBIRs on VFX fan and TVC combustor technologies, as well as Phase I SBIR program on active tip clearance. In addition, Dr. Mehta has also led CFX based CFD efforts on Phase I and Phase II programs that focused on developing an innovative rotating seal, and has contributed to other SBIR programs aimed at developing innovative UAV compressor, combustor (TVC based), and turbine technologies. In addition to significant experience in computational combustion, Dr. Mehta has also led efforts that involved turbine blade film cooling, as well as design and analysis of combustor rigs. Turbine aero and cooling has also been another area of expertise, where Dr. Mehta has contributed. These include, blade film cooling, S1 shroud cooling, as well as GE90 S1 nozzle cooling. Variable Turbine Nozzle has also been another area, in which Dr. Mehta has been instrumental in developing some innovative fluidics concepts.

comments:
Each year, the CRC empowers more than 30,000 individuals to live a more sustainable life. The CRC reaches out to and engages these individuals through programming in its energy, water, and waste divisions:

CRC’s Energy Division promotes energy conservation, energy efficiency and renewable energy. This includes residential energy advising, hosting educational seminars, and organizing the annual Boulder County Tour of Sustainable Homes. The energy division’s ReNew Our Schools program promotes energy education and conservation in local schools, granting solar electric systems to select schools each year.

CRC’s Water Division helps residents and businesses reduce water consumption by encouraging the efficient use of water. The Slow the Flow Colorado Program offers free sprinkler inspections and indoor water evaluations to customers of partner water providers. The Garden-In-A-Box Program sells professionally-designed, pre-planned xeric gardens to make xeriscaping easy. Free Water-Wise Landscape Seminars in April cover xeriscaping and sustainable landscaping topics.  Each year, the xeric garden program helps to convert 40,000 square feet of high-water-use landscape to xeriscape.

CRC’s ReSource Division manages two salvage yards (in Boulder and Fort Collins) that accept donations and sell reclaimed building materials to the public. Promoting waste reduction through innovative landfill diversion programs, ReSource sells these reclaimed materials at 50%–90% below retail cost. Both ReSource Yards serve as drop-off locations for homeowners and contractors. Located in Boulder, the ReSource Tool Library is open daily and lets members borrow from a diverse tool inventory at affordable rates. The ReSource Tool Library also offers Tool School classes. Professionals at ReSource Deconstruction Services facilitate the sustainable practice of carefully dismantling a structure, while preserving the structure’s embodied energy and yielding materials for reuse. WoodWorks sells affordable, high quality wood products produced from salvaged materials.

In the mid 2000’s, I took the initiative to start a business that addressed passive energy efficiency and home performance work. In 2008, there were only 22 registered energy raters in the entire state of Colorado on Colorado’s Estar website. Energy raters use HERS rating energy modeling software to evaluate how a pre built residential home will consume fossil fuel energy. Which is different than energy auditing , which evaluate energy loss/consumption of an existing home. 
Energy Auditing was in its infancy in 2008, and the non-profit “Center for Resource Conservation” in Boulder, CO offered its citizens, subsidized energy audits. The problem was, once the audit report was given to the home owner and all the recommendations that follow, no company existed to actually perform the work. Thus the niche to exploit and the creation of Advanced Air Sealing LLC came to be.


Advanced Air Sealing realizes there are additional choices in having the work completed. The experience and knowledge our company provides for this particular kind of work, is second best to none. 
  
Our Standards of practice are based on BPI and Home Performance W Energy Star for new-builds and existing residential construction.  This check list covers over 22 thermal bypasses typically created during the building of platform framed homes.  

According to the Department of Energy, the average American home leaks 60% of its air per hour.  The inefficiency is not the result of poorly insulated attics and walls, but escaping “conditioned air” resulting in the largest waste.  The work proposed, will not only add considerable comfort to your home but should reduce your annual energy bills (electric & gas) by 18 to 25 percent.   

The Advanced Air Sealing crew understands the importance of treating the customer and the customer’s home with respect and courtesy.  We take care in meeting special instructions while working in your home.   

Feel free to contact us with additional questions or set up a project start date.  You may reach us at 303.587.9493 or email- Airseal@comcast.net or website www.thisairsealedhome.com  If you plan to hire Advanced Air Sealing, please read, sign and return the Service Agreement that accompanies the email. We look forward to speaking with you soon.

GenCore Candeo, Ltd.  is a small business  that develops application software product  tools for system owners and individual agencies.  We provide diagnostic functionality for Cassidian, Raytheon, and Motorola MotoTRBO, SmartNet, SmartZone, OmniLink, ASTRO25 and Dimetra systems by monitoring, managing, archiving and reporting radio communication system data from the Control Channel over the air or the ATIA port over the wire.  

The simple answer: we make life much easier for system owners and operators with leading edge communication system management solutions. 

These are commercially available, 100% Microsoft Windows based software tools which run on an office-standard desktop PC or server.  Each feature and module can be purchased separately or in some cases, as part of a package of features.  The input modules handle all of the logistics of sending the data out to other networked copies.  The design chosen depends on network topology, call volume and mission critical nature.  

Additional software modules can:

-Identify and eliminate duplicate cloned radios that are stealing airtime from a radio system
-Reload data in the event of a system crash with access to backup data files 
-Solve the problem of software and hardware time synchronization through use of a windows service and configuration program
-Display a geospacial overview of a trunking network with real-time radio system activity and site conditions such as triggered events and alarms
-Provide a level views of radio network site conditions, such as triggered events or alarms
-Filter and organize radio system data and send it to another system device
-Add a remote console to the radio system as an operator
-Filter radio system data stream and deliver this securely over the web to an end user agency
-Retroactively view the health of the hardware then analyze trends 
-Provide forensic reporting on all radio traffic data
-Provision, manage and bill end user agencies on the radio system
-Provide an interface for MCC7500 users and implement these features into an integrated software and hardware solution for dispatcher effectiveness

Kurtis Edwards

Weisflock Aviation

comments:
Red Team USA, Inc, was formed by two seasoned computer specialists: Nick Krut and Frank Hare.  At a time in their lives when most folks look to retiring schemes, Krut and Hare’s scheme is to help small companies protect themselves from cyber criminals.  

To start, Hare and Krut spent two-years researching, “why there are chronic levels of virus and malware attacks on professional client networks and personal computers.”  Unfortunately, the solutions they sought could not be found through industry-standard antivirus mechanisms and channels, in and of themselves. 

As engineers, Hare and Krut realized that they had to either discover and/or create out-of-the-box solutions.  Over a 3-year time period, they developed a process to help protect computers from cyber intrusions initiated by cyber criminals.  Their 4th year of scientific cyber protection research involved the implementation of their processes on select clients from their existing client bases, and “eureka”, the protection system worked as expected: a new, well-needed, cyber security service was born.

Hare and Krut then incorporated Red Team USA, Inc, in 2010, with a mission statement, “to help provide the highest cyber crime protection for businesses and individuals at the least possible cost”.

Krut and Hare recognized that the small business could not afford the same level of cyber security expense as the Fortune 500 companies.  Still, though, small businesses do need the same level of protection as the large companies.  So, they designed a system that resulted in a unique pay-by-subscription model.  The subscription service enables Red Team USA to offer “enterprise-type” IT security protection to small companies (1-to-100 workstations) for far, far less.  Red Team USA’s daily cost-per-computer workstation starts for less than what a cup of coffee per day can be. 

This is how the Red Team USA cyber security process works: 1) a cyber security vulnerability test and an assessment are performed on a prospect’s internet/network; 2) these tests reveal the weaknesses (holes) in a personal computer or network, and indicate to Red Team USA’s technicians what level of protection is needed; 3) Red Team USA then designs and implements its proprietary and customized cyber protection on a “per-computer workstation-per-day” subscription basis; 4) Red Team USA then provides ongoing “perimeter” Guardian-type intrusion detection/protection services between the internet and the client’s local network; 5) alerts about cyber intrusion issues can be sent to the client upon unusual cyber activity (or intrusion impact), as well as a comprehensive monthly report and suggested resolutions, if any.

Red Team USA is continually updated about cyber-threat prevention through its membership with resources as the Information Systems Security Assn (ISSA), the F.B.I’s Cyber Security partnership, Infragard.



 

Krut and Hare’s relentless research innovation and hard work has led Red Team USA to be Colorado’s premier and only proactive Cyber Security Resource (MSSP) that offers cyber security protection on a subscription basis. 

Red Team USA is a recommended Veteran-owned vendor and Cyber Security Company.  Red Team USA’s Security Policy does not allow Red Team USA to divulge its partner or its client list, but clients include artists, engineering firms, CPA networks, law offices, retailers, a building management company and Aerospace Manufacturer. 

Red Team USA is continually expanding its exploration about how to best serve its clients.  In 2011 Red Team USA created a Cyber Security Consortium of leading Cyber Security Practitioners to provide unparalleled services that are critical to maintain a Cyber-secure environment.

    2)CEO/CFO, Mid-Level management and emp

KimiaPower is a small business consulting engineering firm specializing in reliability, availability and maintainability (RAM) analysis, reliability engineering education and power system design and engineering. KimiaPower offerings include:
	· Performing reliability analysis for components and systems
	· Assisting our clients in developing and implementing Design for Reliability (DFR) tools and procedures.
	· Implementing Reliability, Availability and Maintainability (RAM) analysis for new product development initiatives.
	· Leading site Root Cause Analysis (RCA) on part failures.
	· Performing probabilistic risk analysis (PRA).

II. Temporary-to-Hire 
TTMP Corporation is the employer of all temporaries we send to supplement the Client work force. TTMP Corporation will pay the wages of the temporaries and is responsible for withholding all income and social security taxes, and paying insurance taxes, the employee’s share of the social security taxes, and benefits normally provided by TTMP Corporation. In addition, TTMP Corporation shall maintain Workman’s Compensation and general liability insurance coverage. If Client and the candidate would prefer a temporary-to-hire agreement, the candidate will be billed at an hourly rate agreed upon between TTMP Corporation and Client for a period of four to six months. If the candidate converts to full-time after this period, there will be no placement fee. Should the candidate convert to full-time prior to the pre-determined period, TTMP Corporation’s fee would be prorated over the remaining portion of the period. Dear Sir or Madame:

I am an exceptional power electronics specialist looking for a new business relationship.  I have invented converter circuits that offer advantages in both size and efficiency.  If you want to produce products with higher power density and higher efficiency than any products currently commercially available, higher reliability products with added value that will give your company a competitive advantage over the rest of the industry, then we should talk.  I am also open to other new business opportunities including power converter product design and development, trouble shooting, consulting and advising, and in-house technical seminars.  Let me know how I can help you.

About me:  I have 31 issued patents and several others pending.  One of my areas of expertise where I feel that I am uniquely qualified in the industry is in the area of topology selection and design trade off decision making.  If there is one area that I have found in which the top industry experts often get it wrong it is the area of topology selection and design trade off decision making.  Other areas of exceptional expertise include high density and high efficiency power supply design, soft switching (also known as Zero Voltage Switching (ZVS)) technology, both isolated and non-isolated solid state lighting applications, and electromagnetic compatibility (EMC).  I have taught many seminars at the Applied Power Electronics Conference and the Power Systems World Conference, most of which were the highest attended seminars and three of which were standing room only.  My seminar topics included gate driver design, soft switching power converters, high efficiency design, and EMC for power supplies.  I have published many conference papers, a series of articles in Power Electronics Technology (PET) magazine on EMC for power conversion and another article series in PET magazine on numerical topology selection which describes a mathematical model I developed for comparing and scoring circuit topologies so that a designer can choose the optimal topology for a given application, based on the operating conditions.  One of my recent inventions describes circuits intended for minimum size solid state lighting which can achieve power factor correction and simultaneously drive multiple independently regulated LED strings using a single magnetic circuit element. I have also designed an integrated circuit (IC) gate driver for SiC VJFETs and SiC bipolar transistors (AAC611 by ASIC Advantage, Inc. (AAI).  AAI is now part of Microsemi), which includes driver, control, and configuration circuits and a switching power supply that generates both positive and negative drive voltages from a single positive power source using only the IC and a few external components which includes a small single winding inductor.  My most recent work has focused on achieving low cost power converters with higher density and higher efficiency than any products currently available for DC/DC applications and for AC/DC applications with and without power factor correction (PFC).  Some of the soft switching circuits I have invented can achieve lower conduction losses, elimination of drain circuit switching losses, low parts count, reduced magnetic circuit element size and cost, and EMC advantages compared to the best circuits commercially available today.  My first patent, now expired, is in widespread use commercially.  That patent revealed a flyback converter that could achieve zero voltage switching (ZVS) without the large conduction losses of the prior invention which required reversal of magnetizing current to achieve ZVS.  My invention could achieve ZVS without incurring large conduction losses because it did not require that the magnetizing current be reversed in order to achieve ZVS.

BKi’s expertise in programmatic support for advanced power and renewable energy, clean transportation, and energy efficiency RD&D is ideally suited to NREL’s mission to develop sustainable energy solutions and facilitate knowledge transfer to address the nation’s energy and environmental challenges. 

For more than 30 years, BKi has:

•	Conducted research on energy efficiency in buildings  and managed the design and implementation of large multi-sponsor EE programs

•	Technical writing and editing and graphics/video development

•	Energy efficiency program design and implementation

BKi has proven its value by providing long-term technical management and communications support to organizations such as the Electric Power Research Institute, the California Energy Commission, and DOE federal laboratories.

I own and have available for sale nearly 5,000 tons of clean, untreated, kiln-dried hardwood mill edgings which can be re-processed to fill a variety of custom biomass orders, ie. feedstock/fuel for alternative heat systems.  On an annual basis I recover and deliver over 900 tons of clean, high-grade hardwood sawdust to industrial, food production, municipal and retail clients of varying sizes.  My goal is."carbon-negative" environmental impact rather than "carbon-neutral".  I believe that properly re-purposing waste wood enables us to reclaim/upcycle its bio-energy and reduce CO2 and methane emissions while lessening man's carbon footprint through carbon sequestration and reduced pressure on landfill space,  I contract with public and private entities to perform industrial and commercial untreated wood cleanups.  My client list includes Clean Harbors, Xcel Energy, Waupaca Northwoods, Metro Wastewater Treatment District (Denver), Morning Fresh Farms, Gilpin (CO) County, Washington (CO) County, and several private companies.  I want to supply suitable wood material to NREL for near-term industrial heating use and also longer-term research applications to achieve a cleaner world.

PM Services Company (PMSC), a Woman-Owned Small Business has been in operation since March, 1986. PMSC provides full facility support services and an expanding range of support services for commercial properties throughout the United States, which include but are not limited to operations & maintenance, energy management and mechanical maintenance on items such as refrigeration equipment and Building Automation Systems (BAS). In order to better serve a complex and technical market, PMSC recently developed the Building Professional Services (BPS) which is a division of PMSC, and employs individuals with a wide range of skills and expertise. PMSC’s BPS division is financially independent but also provides value-added services to our O&M or complete facilities management. Each member of the division maintains professional certifications to substantiate their abilities. Certifications include, but are not limited to ASHRAE’s Commissioning Process Management Professional Certification (CPMP), Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design (LEED), Certified Energy Managers (CEM), Certified Demand Side Managers (CDSM), and Professional Engineers (PE). Our members are required to stay current on technology and each member of the division maintains memberships to professional organizations including Association of Energy Engineers, and American Society of Heating, Refrigeration, and Air-Conditioning Engineers (ASHRAE). With a diverse background, many members of our professional services division are veterans in energy management, building management systems, and smart building technology. We fully understand what is required to maintain and improve state-of-the-art buildings.

Greetings, 

As a renowned energy laboratory, we request a partnership on transitioning our game-changing microgrid-based prototype to scalable sizes for both military and civil applications. 

We require a qualified tech transfer office and lab to assist our minority-owned company with the tech-to-market process of our 340W 576Wh mobile microgrid.

Currently, we have a working desktop model of a Self-Contained, Air-to-Electricity Mobile Microgrid that utilizes only $.05 per kwh of electricity during its isothermal-based (rather than convention toxic-based combustible) conversion phase. The genius lies in the ability of dropping it anywhere to generate electricity and store both 0-emission heat and electricity simultaneously. The mobile microgrid utilizes storable, surrounding resources to generate and store electricity anytime onsite. 

We would like a partnership to scale to size the portable system for multiple military and civilian applications, including handheld, outdoor, residential, commercial, industrial, regional and electric vehicle power applications.  Our 21st century world can be energized by the Power of Air, while we create jobs and profit through cheaper power purchasing agreements with utilities, the sale of $.05 per kwh generation usage fee, and leasing fees.   

Please visit our website for more info, including pictures and videos. Thank you and we look forward to your reply. 

Best regards,

Varnell M. Castor
Monkeytech International LLC
